        <section id="uses-comp">
            <h>complement</h>
            <p>Like other nouns, <g>sgoil</g> can be used as the complement of a <a
                    href="?xx=prepositions/prepositions">preposition</a>.</p>
            <p>Examples with <g><a href="?gd=an^preposition">ann an</a> sgoil</g>
                <en>in a school</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha an gille beag <m>anns an sgoil</m>.</gd>
                        <tr>The little boy is in the school.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 14 [adapted]</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>A bheil Seònaid <m>anns an sgoil</m> an diugh?</gd>
                        <tr>Is Janet in the school today?</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 14</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
    </section>


